# Monitoring Stack: Prometheus & Grafana on Kubernetes

A complete monitoring solution using Prometheus Operator, kube-state-metrics, and Grafana via the `kube-prometheus-stack` Helm chart.

## 🔧 Installation

### Prerequisites
- Kubernetes cluster
- `kubectl` configured
- Helm 3+

### Steps

1. **Set up a local Kubernetes cluster (if not already running)**
   - Install [Docker Desktop](https://www.docker.com/products/docker-desktop/) (includes Kubernetes) or [Minikube](https://minikube.sigs.k8s.io/docs/start/)
   - Enable Kubernetes in Docker Desktop or start Minikube:
     ```bash
     minikube start --driver=docker
     ```

2. **Install Helm (if not installed)**
   ```bash
   brew install helm   